<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="24071" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="24071">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="24071">
New species record for Arkansas. This 
<taxonomicName genus="Asteraceae" lsidName="Asteraceae" pageId="0" pageNumber="24071" rank="genus">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
specialist occurs throughout most of the western half of the US; our specimens represent the easternmost location of the species published to date (
<bibRefCitation author="Hurd, Paul David" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="24071" pagination=": 15" title="Principal sunflower bees of North America with emphasis on the Southwestern United States (Hymenoptera, Apoidea)" volume="310" year="1980">Hurd et al. 1980</bibRefCitation>
), but they have been collected in some parts of Mississippi (Dr. Katherine Parys 2018, pers. comm., 8 February). Opportunistic (Table 1: Sites 5, 7-11, 15-18).
</paragraph>
